## Weekly Operating Rhythm

As a solo founder, discipline in time allocation is the difference between momentum and chaos. This is the weekly cadence from Day 11 onward.

|Day      |Morning Block (3hrs)                               |Afternoon Block (3hrs)                  |Evening Block (1–2hrs)                       |
|---------|---------------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------|
|Monday   |Review KPI dashboard + pipeline. Prioritize week   |Operator outreach (new listings)        |Content creation (1 Arabic article draft)    |
|Tuesday  |Client follow-ups (proposals, quotes, deposits)    |HNWI outreach (WhatsApp, LinkedIn)      |Instagram content (2 posts + Stories)        |
|Wednesday|Client consultations (calls, yacht matching)       |Co-broker partner calls                 |Facebook community posting                   |
|Thursday |B2B outreach (hotels, agencies, corporate)         |Platform improvements (UX, new listings)|Content creation (article editing/publishing)|
|Friday   |Client follow-ups + pipeline cleanup               |SEO review + Arabic keyword tracking    |Instagram + Stories                          |
|Weekend  |Respond to inquiries only (< 4hr SLA still applies)|Light content batching for next week    |Rest. Sustainability matters                 |

### Time Allocation Rule (60/30/10)

|Allocation            |% of Time|Activities                                                                           |
|----------------------|---------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|**Revenue-generating**|**60%**  |Client outreach, follow-ups, proposals, closing deals, operator relationship building|
|Marketing             |30%      |Content, social media, SEO, influencer outreach, Facebook community, Instagram       |
|Platform/Admin        |10%      |Technical improvements, CRM maintenance, legal, admin, accounting                    |

